-- Ex-divs to take 1.5 points off FTSE 100 on Sept. 24
-- By Sudip Kar-Gupta
-- Mon Sep 22, 2014 06:13AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, Sept 22 (Reuters) - The following FTSE 100 <.FTSE> companies will go ex-dividend on Wednesday, after which investors will no longer qualify for the latest dividend payout.

According to Reuters calculations at current market prices, the effect of the resulting adjustment to prices by market-makers would take 1.49 points off the index. COMPANY   (RIC)  DIVIDEND  STOCK OPTION   IMPACT   (pence)CENTRICA  <CNA.L>  5.10   1.013  OLD MUTUAL<OML.L>  2.45   0.472Among FTSE 250 <.FTMC> companies going ex-dividend are:COMPANY  (RIC)DIVIDEND(pence)  ALENT<ALNT.L>  3.00  BOVIS HOMES  <BVS.L>  12.00  CREST NICHOLSON  <CRST.L>  4.10  DRAX <DRX.L>   4.70  DIGNITY  <DTY.L>   6.49  ESSENTRA <ESNT.L>  5.70  KIER <KIE.L>  49.50  LADBROKES<LAD.L>   4.30  OXFORD INSTRUMENTS   <OXIG.L>  9.04